<TITLE> Stocks return to losses </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 31 (bdnews24.com)Markets returned to losses on Tuesday after witnessing brief gains the previous day. Almost all the sectors saw a price fall as investors were busy selling-off holdings, said brokerage house officials. "Retail investors are panicked on reports of gloomy economic forecasts," an official of Anwar Securities told bdnews24.com. Market operators say the selling spree came to reap profits. "Investors sold-off to make profits out of the last day's gains," DSE senior vice president Saiful Islam said. He ruled out 'panic-selling'. Turnover up, indices down The prime bourse saw 18, 684,474 shares worth Tk 3.25 billion changing hands, up from Monday's Tk 2.75 billion. The DSE general index maintained a downward curve across the day. The DGEN or general index lost 29.89 points or 1.20 percent on 2446.92. The DSI or all share price index closed at 2033.30, down 22.11 points or 1.07 percent. The blue-chip DSE-20 fell 32.29 points or 1.67 percent to 1891.49. Losers outnumbered gainers 166 to 74 while four issues held steady. CSE Indices on Chittagong Stock Exchange also ended downbeat due to losses in leather, banks, ceramic and paper shares. The CSCX or selective categories index fell 71.20 points or 1.43 percent to close at 4884.83. The CASPI or all share price index ended on 7578.30, slumping 98.05 points or 1.27 percent. The CSE-30 blue-chip index lost 68.37 points or 1.16 percent to finish at 5790.30. Of the traded issues, 110 declined, 41 advanced with five scrips unchanged. Turnover on the commercial capital's bourse reached Tk 396.206 million from trading of 3,466,516 sharesdown from Tk 424.67 million the previous day. DSE's top ten by turnover Summit Power topped the board with a turnover of Tk 220.346 million. It crept down 0.32 percent to Tk 1089. S Alam Cold Rolled Steels followed, with turnover of Tk 165.065 million, to end 3.68 percent up at Tk 612. Summit Alliance Port Ltd surged 11 percent to Tk 1931 with a turnover of Tk 132.898 million. Beximco had shares worth Tk 131.623 million traded and ended on Tk 202.80, edging down 0.92 percent. Aftab Automobiles had shares worth Tk 111.137 million traded and gained 9.40 percent to end on Tk 1222. Other scrips on the turnover board Apex Adelchi Footwear, DESCO, Eastern Housing Ltd, BSRM Steels and Titas Gasfell as investors locked in profits.
